---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Craft Services — Eliyannah Amirah Yisrael"
  description="The fun room. Recipes, reading, playlists, Chicago, YouTube."
  pageSlug="craft"
  pageNumber={7}
>

<main class="main">
  <section class="page">
    <div class="page-eyebrow">Section 07 · Craft Services</div>
    <h1 class="page-title">Craft <em>Services</em></h1>
    <p class="page-subtitle">
      The table in the hallway. Where the crew actually meets each other.
    </p>

    <p style="max-width: 640px; font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--ink-soft); margin-bottom: 2rem;">
      On a set, craft services is where you figure out who everybody is. Here: the things outside the work that are still very much the work. The recipes. The books. The playlists. The Chicago spots. A room kept deliberately fun on a serious site.
    </p>

    <div class="craft-menu">

      <div class="craft-item">
        <div class="craft-item-number">01</div>
        <div class="craft-item-label">The Recipe</div>
        <h3 class="craft-item-title">The <em>chocolate chip cookie</em> that won.</h3>
        <div class="craft-item-body">
          <span class="prompt">Name the cookie recipe. Not the generic Toll House version — <em>your</em> version. The one with the browned butter or the flaky salt or the night-long rest. A sentence of why it wins. A link to the recipe if it's public, or a "drop me a line and I'll send it" if it's not.</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="craft-item">
        <div class="craft-item-number">02</div>
        <div class="craft-item-label">The Reading List</div>
        <h3 class="craft-item-title">What's <em>open</em> on the nightstand right now.</h3>
        <div class="craft-item-body">
          <span class="prompt">Three to five books. Actual current reading. A novel, a memoir, a work of criticism, a trade book on the industry, a cookbook. The list from the voice map — Sophie Kinsella next to Toni Morrison — is the register to hit.</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="craft-item">
        <div class="craft-item-number">03</div>
        <div class="craft-item-label">The Building Playlist</div>
        <h3 class="craft-item-title">The <em>soundtrack</em> for making a forest.</h3>
        <div class="craft-item-body">
          <span class="prompt">A short description of what's on rotation while you work. A Spotify or Apple Music link if you have a public playlist for this. A line of context — what the playlist is for, what the mood is.</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="craft-item">
        <div class="craft-item-number">04</div>
        <div class="craft-item-label">The Chicago Map</div>
        <h3 class="craft-item-title">The <em>spots</em> I defend in court.</h3>
        <div class="craft-item-body">
          <span class="prompt">Five Chicago places you actually love and go to. A restaurant. A bookstore. A neighborhood. A museum. A barbershop or salon you trust. One line each. The geographic specificity is the whole point.</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="craft-item">
        <div class="craft-item-number">05</div>
        <div class="craft-item-label">The Watch List</div>
        <h3 class="craft-item-title">What I <em>just saw</em> and can't stop thinking about.</h3>
        <div class="craft-item-body">
          <span class="prompt">One film or TV show, currently. Not a capsule review. A sentence on the one specific thing it's teaching you about the work. (The voice map note — "not just watching, studying" — applies here.)</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="craft-item">
        <div class="craft-item-number">06</div>
        <div class="craft-item-label">The YouTube Channel</div>
        <h3 class="craft-item-title">Sunshine <em>Moxie</em> on YouTube.</h3>
        <div class="craft-item-body">
          <p>The beginning of the Sunshine Moxie cultural commentary show — Cultural Curiosity and Commentary in video form. Currently in development. Existing work and older videos already live on the channel.</p>
          <p style="margin-top: 0.75rem;"><a href="https://www.youtube.com/@SunshineMoxie" style="color: var(--ink); border-bottom: 2px solid var(--kodak); text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600;">@SunshineMoxie →</a></p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>
</main>

</BaseLayout>
